title: Grateful Dead Live at Zoo Amphitheater on 1981-07-05
description:
Set 2

Samson & Delilah, Don't Ease Me In-> The Music Never Stopped, Ship of Fools-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> He's Gone-> Drums-> The Other One-> Stella Blue-> Around & Around-> Johnny B. Goode, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: recorded with Sony TC  D5-M , not NAK 550 recorded with Sony TC  D5-M , not NAK 550

Zoo Amphitheater  This was my first GD show. I was 17 and just out of high school. Before the show an old hippie dressed in psychedelic overalls was walking through the crowd quaking like a duck, passing out four-way hits of Donald Duck acid. He gave me a four-way. Told me to take one and pass the other three out. Me being 17 and never had eaten acid before, of course took the entire four. way; I've been a dead head ever since.

really good show, first set especially Carriacou's story touched my heart... and tickled my phunny bone! 
Haven't heard this recording but was reading reviews and couldn't not give credit where due!

AMAZING Aud This is one of the best audience tapes I've ever heard. It's simply perfect and once again Ohr Weinberg's work captured the vocals and tones of Jerry, Bobby and Phil beautifully. The separation is superb and it's easy to pick out Bobby ... So great that he's releasing more and more of his work ... so needless to say that I think this is the best aud available ...
